Topic:		language/lex

Description:	The Lex Programming Language

Notes:

  Lex (and its GNU descendent, flex) is a generator of lexical analysis code.
  It translates a set of patterns (regular expressions) and snippets of C code
  into a compilable set of C routines for scanning an input stream and
  breaking it into tokens.

